content:
Improve customer service and agent training with sentiment analysis of call conversations. Agents and supervisors can view turn-by-turn sentiment alongside the call recording from a previous conversation. Supervisors can easily spot moments when the customer or agent isnâ€™t happy, listen to the corresponding recorded call segments, and then provide better agent training.

This feature is available for Salesforce orgs in the North America region only. It's available with Service Cloud Voice and Amazon Connect telephony models.

After a call ends, you can view the customer and agent sentiments in the Call Audio Player. Each utterance can have a positive, negative, or neutral sentiment. For example, to identify what was said when negative sentiments occur, play the recording at those moments.

Complete these tasks before setting up Sentiment Journey:

* Verify that Contact Lens is enabled on Amazon Connect.
* Create an EventBridge rule for Amazon Sentiment Signals.
* Enable agents and supervisors to view sentiments of call conversations by adding the Call Audio Player to the Voice Call page layout.

Verify that Contact Lens is enabled in your contact flows. Verify that you have Amazon Web Services IAM admin permissions with the ability to create Amazon EventBridge rules. Upgrade your contact center to at least version 10.0.

Create an EventBridge rule:

* From the AWS Management Console, go to Amazon EventBridge | Rules.
* Click Create rule.
* In the Define rule detail screen, give the rule a name and optional description.
* In the Build event pattern screen, scroll down to the Event pattern section and click Custom patterns (JSON editor).
* Copy the following JSON sample event and paste it into the Event pattern text box:
	+ {"detail-type": ["Object Created"], "source": ["aws.s3"], "detail": { "bucket": { "name": ["contactcenter-694266641768"] }, "object": {"key": [{"prefix": "Analysis/Voice"}]} } }
* Click Next.
* In the Select target(s) screen, set the Select a target dropdown to Lambda function, and set the Function to the PostCallAnalysisTriggerFunction.
* Click Next twice.

After configuring Contact Lens settings and EventBridge rule:

* When a customer hangs up from a voice call, Contact Lens processes the call data and saves the transcript file to the contact center Amazon S3 bucket.
* Every time a file is added to the S3 bucket, the EventBridge rule triggers the PostCallAnalysisTriggerFunction Lambda function to read the files in the S3 bucket, prepare the data, and save the data to the Salesforce database.

Enable agents and supervisors to view sentiments of call conversations:

* Add the Call Audio Player to the Voice Call page layout.
* You can also add the Agent Sentiment Score and Customer Sentiment Score fields to the Voice Call page layout.
title: Improving Customer Service with Sentiment Analysis in Service Cloud
